step_data.thought:
I can see that the Layers menu is now open, as indicated by the heading 'Map Layers' (element [207]) being visible. The menu shows several different map layer options that I can explore. I can see four different layer options listed:

1. Standard (element [228])
2. CyclOSM (element [246])
3. ÖPNVKarte (element [264])
4. Humanitarian (element [282])

Each of these represents a different visualization style for the map. To explore these different layers, I should click on each one to see how the map visualization changes for New York City. Let's start by clicking on the CyclOSM layer since we're currently on the Standard layer (which appears to be the default).
